# Project Conventions

## Branch Naming

Format: `<type>/<username>/<issue-number>-<short-desc>`

```
feat/hrithik-gavankar/11-auth
fix/hrithik-gavankar/7-empty-response
```

## Commit Messages

Format: `<type>(FA-<issue>): <short description>`

- `FA` = Fitness Agent (project prefix), number maps to GitHub issue
- Scope `(FA-<n>)` is optional for changes not tied to an issue

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| feat | New feature |
| fix | Bug fix |
| refactor | Code restructuring, no behavior change |
| docs | Documentation only |
| chore | Build, CI, deps |
| style | Formatting, whitespace |
| test | Tests |

```
feat(FA-11): add Google & GitHub OAuth login via Supabase Auth
fix(FA-7): resolve agent returning empty response
chore: bump supabase-py to 2.x
```

## Pull Requests

- Title follows commit format: `feat(FA-11): add OAuth login`
- Body must include `Closes #<issue>` to auto-link and auto-close
- Attach screenshots for UI changes
- One feature or fix per PR

## Secrets

Never commit `.env`, `.auth_storage.json`, or `secrets.toml`. All secrets load via `os.environ.get()`.
